# Caddy reverse proxy → uvicorn, with automatic HTTPS (Let's Encrypt).
#
# Replace the hostname below. Two easy ways to get a valid cert:
#   • You own a domain: use e.g.  api.yourdomain.com  (point its DNS A record
#     at this box's IP first).
#   • No domain: use sslip.io — the hostname IS the IP, so a box at
#     203.0.113.9 becomes  203-0-113-9.sslip.io  and Caddy gets a real cert
#     for it with zero DNS setup.
#
# Then: sudo caddy reload --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile

REPLACE-ME.sslip.io {
    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8080
}
